Background•Hospital overcrowding is an issue that affects hospitals all over the world.•Overcrowding leads to inferior patient outcomes.•A method of accurately predicting patient length of stay would be helpful to hospital administrators in bed allocation strategies.
Innovation•Previous papers1,2detailed length of stay (LOS) prediction for patients with specificdiagnoses (hip-fracture, cardiac patients).•We generalizeLOS prediction for a wider range of patients.

References1.Daghistani, T.A., et al., Predictors of in-hospital length of stay among cardiac patients: A machine learning approach. Int J Cardiol, 2019. 288: p. 140-147.2.Elbattah, M. and O. Molloy, Using Machine Learning to Predict Length of Stay and Discharge Destination for Hip-Fracture Patients. 2016. 207-217.
•2016 Statewide Planning and Research Cooperative System (SPARCS)•2,000,000+ New York State Inpatient Records•Variables: Age, Sex, Race, Diagnosis,Insurance Type,Risk of Mortality
Model Architecture•Use Weibull distribution to more closely match LOS distribution.•Include more diagnosis specific information to increase predictive power.
